HEADWORD: Archenteron
<hw>Arch`en"ter*on</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>arch-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ intestine.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The primitive
enteron or undifferentiated digestive sac of a gastrula or other embryo.
